<div class="entry">
<img src=/imagesvr_ce/102/secure_VPN_lock.jpg  style="float:left;margin:2px;width:300px;height:200px;"/>
<p> A <a href="http://www.webopedia.com/TERM/V/VPN.html">Virtual Private network (VPN)</a> uses a public network (usually the Internet) to connect securely to a private network (such as a company's network) to communicate confidentially over the public network.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Using a VPN will let you share files and resources &ndash; including voice, video or data files -- as though you were physically connected on the same network. It's a good option for remote workers and organizations with global offices and partners to share data in a private manner.</p></div>
<div class="excerpt_entry_footer"> <a href="/Blog/Tech-FAQ/how-to-create-a-secure-business-vpn.html">Read More</a></div>
