<div class="entry">
<img src=/imagesvr_ce/5427/RAM210x150.jpg  style="float:left;margin:2px;width:300px;height:200px;"/>
<p> </p>
<p>One of the questions that Webopedia has been asked a few times on our Facebook Page is to explain the difference between RAM and ROM. RAM (<a href="http://www.webopedia.com/TERM/R/RAM.html">Random Access Memory</a>) and ROM (<a href="http://www.webopedia.com/TERM/R/ROM.html">Read Only Memory</a>) are types of computer memory that provide users with access to information stored on a computer. Here are the top five differences between the two types of memory:</p></div>
